<br>
The cleric and chanter both wanted the SK to tank since he could get agro a lot faster than I could and only had about 750 hps less than me. (He and I were the same level in similar gear).<br>
<br>
Everyone in the group sympathised with me about warriors not being desired to tank anymore. But they also agreed that the chanter needed to not die (as did I) when he slowed and that in order for that to happen the group needed the sk to get quick agro and just go ahead and tank.<br>
<br>
So anyone who says warriors don't have an agro problem in pop is just burrying their head in the sand. We have a problem, other classes recognize this. They aren't willing to play around our problem if they don't have to. We are no longer wanted to tank in exp groups unless there isn't a paladin or sk around. <br>
<br>
Denying the situation will not make it go away. Unfortunatly, even admiting it wont make it go away, only the devs will do that, and frankly they don't give a damn. <p>Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
