<br>
No.  Actually you are the one that needs to calm down and take a breath.  Are life taps game breaking or horribly unbalancing?  Hardly.  But I continually see Knights going on about how this or that spell is worthless or doesn't mean anything or doesn't really add to the class.  And I don't buy into it at all.  <br>
<br>
While perhaps one spell selected individually might not seem all that impressive, its the broad spectrum of spells available that make the difference.  Options, utility, ways to do things that make a difference.  Knights have lots of them.  Warriors have a few.  As compensation we're supposed to excell in other ways.  Ways, which with PoP, have become much less meaningful than before, while the things a Knight brings to the table are much more meaningful.  Our advantages, while not insignificant, are being negated to a great degree.  Knight disadvantages, while not insignificant, are also being negated to a great degree.<br>
<br>
You end up with a choice between having a big HP heavy melee that can't hold aggro under all situations or having a lighter HP melee who can hold aggro under almost all situations.  If you don't REALLY need the tank to be that HP heavy, then second choice is the better one.<br>
<br>
Now, you are concerned about your viability in a group?  I don't blame you, I am too.  I don't mind your being viable just so long as it doesn't come at the expense of my viability.  And right now, I believe it does.  Because the difference between the two is too large for people NOT to prefer the Knight over the Warrior.<br>
<br>
