<br>
1.  The fact that the SK had 2200 hp less than the warrior, yet was the more desireable tank because he could control aggro better is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>exactly the way it should be</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  This is because the trials have a lot to do with unrestrained DPS--  Nukers are going absolutely full burn on every mob for 5-10 minutes.  A weaker tank with stronger aggro holding ability is in his natural element here.  An SK <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>should</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be a better tank for the trials-- at least, for the waves.  This is not to say that a warrior shouldn't work, I have done the trials with both a warrior and an SK, but it is definitely slanted towards the SK and there is nothing wrong with this.<br>
<br>
2.  The fact that the warrior with a Twisted Steel Bastard sword could not contribute as much damage as a similarly equipped SK is interesting.  I think a warrior should have the option to deal good damage when he is not being used to tank.  Unless the group was mistaken and the SK wouldn't actually have done more damage, that is a good point.<br>
<br>
3.  I think that it's important to note that the ability to hold aggro becomes far less important on the final boss, and tanking ability becomes more important.  I'd rather have a tank with 6khp over an SK with 4k any day for the prime executioner, no matter how well the SK could hold aggro.  As a mage I'm not going to be so trigger happy on the boss like I was during the waves, I'll be steady and controlled.  A warrior should have no problem holding aggro while I deal considerable damage.  Depending on mana, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>might</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be able to deal damage faster with an SK, but to me it's not worth the risk of killing everyone because the cleric runs out of mana or misses a CH on the 4k tank.<br>
<br>
<br>
Looking at it from the outside in:  If my group wasn't having trouble with the waves but was dieing to the boss every time, I'd look to get a warrior tank or better healer, if my group was falling apart on the waves because the warrior couldn't hold aggro, I'd either look for an SK or more skilled damage dealers. <p><center><br>
